Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Denizli is infrequently afflicted with anthrax in a country where this disease is widespread and enzootic. The last bovine outbreaks were in 2015 and 2006. But Turkey differs from the other European countries by this disease being essentially year round and outbreaks in the colder autumn months are common. If ever a country needed to consider initiating a serious surveillance and control programme for this disease, Turkey should be at the front of the line. Just taking bovine outbreaks there were 60 in 2016 and 54 in 2015, with higher numbers in previous years. Presently only 2 percent of the cattle are vaccinated.

To find Denizli, go to: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denizli_Province. It is south western Turkey within sight of the Aegean; it is part of the Aegean Region. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5448646,87.]
